==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prism glass
<hw>Prism glass</hw>. <def>Glass with one side smooth and the other side
formed into sharp-edged ridges so as to reflect the light that passes
through, used at windows to throw the light into the interior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prismoid</ent>⟦br⟧
